"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016342","Cabinet Office","false","2018-12-04","<p>There are two members of staff who are responsible for photography and filming of official events. Their combined salary is £71,921. They work in a team shared by No10 and the Cabinet Office.</p><p> </p><p>The Cabinet Office and No 10 digital team have 5 staff members where part of their role is the production of films and photography .This type of work accounts for less than 20% of each individual's role.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","196747","2018-12-04T12:27:02.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016342/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016342/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-11-28","Cabinet Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many full-time equivalent staff (a) the Cabinet Office and (b) Number 10 Downing Street employ whose responsibilities include the (i) photography and filming of official events and (ii) production of official photographs and films.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","196746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016343","Cabinet Office","false","2018-12-04","<p>There are two members of staff who are responsible for photography and filming of official events. Their combined salary is £71,921. They work in a team shared by No10 and the Cabinet Office.</p><p> </p><p>The Cabinet Office and No 10 digital team have 5 staff members where part of their role is the production of films and photography .This type of work accounts for less than 20% of each individual's role.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","196746","2018-12-04T12:27:02.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016343/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016343/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-11-28","Cabinet Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the combined annual salaries of all full-time equivalent staff of (a) the Cabinet Office and (b) Number 10 Downing Street whose responsibilities include (i) the photography and filming of official events and (ii) the production of official photographs and films in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","196747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016344","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-05","<p>The nominated undertaker (HS2) will reimburse reasonable costs subject to the conditions outlined in the Information Papers C3 &amp; C14 that were prepared in support of the Phase 1 Act. Please refer to Section 8 of the Information Paper.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-05T11:35:49.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016344/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016344/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016344/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether (a) HS2 Ltd, (b) third party contractors or (c) his Department will be liable in the event that settlement damage to vulnerable and listed buildings occurs due to works along the High Speed Two London tunnel route.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016345","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-03","<p>The Department has received a small number of representations regarding the assessment of the risks in relation to HS2 Ltd’s development of the design of the HS2 tunnels on the Park Village East retaining wall, which is located on the approach to Euston Station.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-03T14:56:32.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016345/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016345/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what representations his Department has received on the risks to buildings along the High Speed Two London tunnel route in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016346","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-03","<p>The total funding envelope of the High Speed 2 project was set at £55.7bn (2015 prices) as part of the 2015 Spending Review settlement.</p><p>The total spend to date is £5.5bn (nominal), inclusive of the financial years 2009-10 to 2017-18.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-03T14:36:53.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016346/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016346/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016346/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his latest estimate is of the total cost of High Speed Two; and how much of that funding has been spent.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016347","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office takes the security of all of our data extremely seriously, including digitised evidence provided by EU Settlement Scheme users. There are processes in place in the Home Office for the capturing and mitigation of risks and vulnerabilities to ensure appropriate control of our services. I can confirm this is the case for the EU Settlement Scheme</p><p>All Home Office systems including EU Exit applications undergo rigorous cyber strengthening prior to launch. This includes an independent security testing to ensure they are resilient to external attack.</p><p>Our IT systems hosting platform include a number of mechanisms to detect and respond to malicious intrusions.</p><p>All data is encrypted both in transit and at rest. Our IT staff are security cleared and data will only be accessed by those who have a valid business reason to access it. The Home Office regularly monitors the systems for abuse and misuse.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-12-07T12:57:18.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016347/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016347/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps his Department has taken to provide assurance to (a) users and (b) employers on the security of documents stored on cloud services in relation to the IT system for applying for settled status.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016348","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions. Regular updates have been provided to the committee and this information is available in the library of the House. [14 people, out of the 164 identified by the Historical Review, were detained in an IRC. 17 people, out of the 164 identified by the Historical Review, were recorded as a voluntary departure].</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196666","2018-12-07T11:13:48.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016348/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016348/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of Windrush people that were held in immigration detention centres.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016349","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions. Regular updates have been provided to the committee and this information is available in the library of the House. [14 people, out of the 164 identified by the Historical Review, were detained in an IRC. 17 people, out of the 164 identified by the Historical Review, were recorded as a voluntary departure].</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196665","2018-12-07T11:13:48.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016349/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016349/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Repatriation: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of Windrush people that participated in voluntary removal.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016350","Cabinet Office","false","2018-12-05","<p>Crown Representatives work with Strategic Suppliers to understand their bid pipeline, and to get market perspectives on particular types of service. Once specific procurements have begun, Crown Representatives do not engage with suppliers on those procurements.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-12-05T10:32:42.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016350/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016350/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-11-28","Interserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the written evidence submitted by Interserve to the Public Accounts Committee on 6 June 2018,  Strategic Suppliers SSU0003, whether Crown Representatives are able to discuss issues relating to contracts not yet awarded with strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","196748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016351","Department for International Development","false","2018-12-05","<p>The Department for International Development has not provided any funding for Radio Dabanga in Sudan since its creation in December 2008. It is largely funded by the Dutch government.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-12-05T17:15:32.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016351/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016351/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-11-28","Sudan: Radio","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government has funded Radio Dabanga in Sudan since its creation in December 2008.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","196749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016352","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-07","<p>The table below provides information on the total expenditure incurred by the High Speed Rail Group on consultancy in support of the HS2 project.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Expenditure</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£2,310</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£4,803,540</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£5,352,792</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>£10,563,780</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>£12,045,048</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>£10,366,823</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>£9,999,662</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br></p><p>The amount spent on consultancy reflects the need to utilise the best specialist expertise to deliver the Government’s biggest investment in transport infrastructure in generations. All consultancy contracts are competitively tendered to ensure value for money and every effort is made to transfer skills to permanent staff and ensure reduced reliance on external contractors.</p><p> </p><p>I am unable to publish a breakdown to your request as this information is commercially sensitive. The Department for Transport has a duty to manage procurements to deliver the best value for the tax payer, and publishing the breakdown requested would be likely to negatively prejudice the effective and efficient outcome of these procurement competitions.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-07T13:28:52.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016352/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016352/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much money his Department has spent on each (a) consultant and (b) consultancy firm to support the HS2 project in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016353","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee. This correspondence is available in the library of the House. The department has not made any assessment of previous employment of those individuals identified by the review, and in many cases the department will not hold this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196668 ; 196669 ; 196670","2018-12-07T11:11:31.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016353/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016353/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of Windrush people that worked in the NHS who were (a) held in immigration detention centres and (b) deported to other countries.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016354","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee. This correspondence is available in the library of the House. The department has not made any assessment of previous employment of those individuals identified by the review, and in many cases the department will not hold this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196667 ; 196669 ; 196670","2018-12-07T11:11:31.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016354/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016354/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of Windrush people that were veterans of the armed forces who were (a) held in immigration detention centres and (b) deported to other countries.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016355","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-03","<p>The Nominated Undertaker (i.e. those acting on behalf of the Secretary of State) will engage with property owners as it is in their combined interest that Settlement Surveys are reflective and factual of the property prior to commencement of tunnel works. The survey will be undertaken by a jointly appointed Independent Chartered Building Surveyor at the nominated undertaker’s cost. This approach was adopted on HS1, Crossrail and Thames Tideway and is a common and recognised practice. See Information Papers C3 &amp; C14 Section 7. The Nominated Undertaker will perform relevant conflict of interest assessments at the appropriate time.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-03T15:53:17.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016355/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016355/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an assessment of the risk of conflicts of interest in relation to settlement deed surveys provided by companies contracted to work on the High Speed Two London Tunnel Route.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016356","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-05","<p>HS2 Ltd has spent nothing on compensation grouting to date. HS2 Ltd has required the contractors to procure tunnel boring machines that are capable of limiting ground movements.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-05T13:36:21.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016356/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016356/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much HS2 Ltd has spent on compensation grouting in advance of construction work along the High Speed Two London tunnel route.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016357","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-03","<p>Universal Credit is calculated and paid on monthly cycles to reflect the fact that the vast majority of people receive their wages monthly. Many social landlords still expect their tenants to pay rent on a weekly basis, a practice based upon a time when both wages and benefits were paid weekly. The effect of this is that, roughly every six years, there will be 53 payment days in a twelve-month period with the result that, over the cycle, the average social sector tenant will receive approximately 35p a week less towards their rent. A key principle of Universal Credit is that it simplifies the benefit system for working age claimants and re-assessing housing costs to reflect the number of rent payments in any particular year would be complicated and lead to confusion. As such, the Department has no plans to amend these regulations.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-12-03T11:17:29.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016357/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016357/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-11-28","Universal Credit: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will amend universal credit regulations to allow for the housing cost element for renters to be calculated for a 53-week year in 2019-20; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","196906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016358","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-05","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-12-05T12:07:45.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016358/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016358/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-28","Speech and Language Therapy: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many speech and language therapists are employed in (a) children and young people’s NHS mental health services and (b) adult NHS mental health services.","false","Biography information for Geraint Davies","Swansea West","Geraint Davies","196658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016359","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee. This correspondence is available in the library of the House. The department has not made any assessment of previous employment of those individuals identified by the review, and in many cases the department will not hold this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196667 ; 196668 ; 196670","2018-12-07T11:11:31.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016359/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016359/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were (a) held in immigration detention centres and (b) deported to other countries who had (i) been teachers and (ii) held other educational positions in the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016360","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee. This correspondence is available in the library of the House. The department has not made any assessment of previous employment of those individuals identified by the review, and in many cases the department will not hold this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196667 ; 196668 ; 196669","2018-12-07T11:11:31.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016360/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016360/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were (a) held in immigration detention centres and (b) deported to other countries who had worked for public transport services in the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016361","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Department does not plan to respond to the report.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-12-07T12:51:18.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016361/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016361/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-28","Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the report entitled Health at a Glance: Europe 2018, published by the OECD on 22 November 2018, whether he plans to respond to the findings on the estimated direct and indirect costs of mental health.","false","Biography information for Geraint Davies","Swansea West","Geraint Davies","196659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016363","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Department has not made an estimate of the overall costs of youth unemployment.</p><p>The most recent data (July-September 2018) from the ONS Labour Force Survey shows that youth unemployment is at a near record low of 476,000 – down by nearly 50% (463,000) since the 2010 election.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-12-07T10:20:44.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016363/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016363/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-11-28","Unemployment: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the cost to the public purse of youth unemployment.","false","Biography information for Geraint Davies","Swansea West","Geraint Davies","196660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016364","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee. This correspondence is available in the library of the House.</p><p>The department has not made any assessment of previous employment of those individuals identified by the historical review, and in many cases the department will not hold this information.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-12-07T12:48:14.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016364/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016364/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Deportation: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were deported to other countries who have since died; and what information he has on their former employment in the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016365","Department for Transport","false","2018-12-03","<p>The actual geotechnical parameters from HS2 project ground investigations have been and are being used for the assessment of buildings impacted by the works. Geotechnical baseline reports (GBR) are not precluded by target cost contracts however their use is not considered relevant for the assessment of the impact of potential ground movement on buildings or associated compensation.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-12-03T14:53:21.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016365/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016365/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-28","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has had discussions with HS2 Ltd on the use of target cost contracts instead of geotechnical baseline reports; and what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the level of compensation arising from damage to vulnerable buildings along the High Speed Two construction route of excluding the use of those reports.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","196827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016366","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee.</p><p>This correspondence is available in the library of the House. As set out in the letter to the Committee of 12 November, the department initially excluded all individuals with a “criminal case type” marker. We reviewed this approach to ensure we have not adopted too broad a definition and revised our methodology. However, individuals who have been deported following a criminal conviction in the UK continue to be excluded from the review.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196674","2018-12-07T12:54:35.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016366/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016366/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Deportation: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were deported to other countries and have family members who are entitled to be in the UK but have been refused entry.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016367","Home Office","false","2018-12-07","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions and have provided regular updates to the committee.</p><p>This correspondence is available in the library of the House. As set out in the letter to the Committee of 12 November, the department initially excluded all individuals with a “criminal case type” marker. We reviewed this approach to ensure we have not adopted too broad a definition and revised our methodology. However, individuals who have been deported following a criminal conviction in the UK continue to be excluded from the review.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196673","2018-12-07T12:54:35.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016367/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016367/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were deported to other countries and have since been refused entry to the UK.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016368","Treasury","false","2018-12-03","<p>The UK and the EU have agreed the Political Declaration, which sets the framework for the UK’s future relationship with the EU. The UK and the EU recognise that this means there could be a spectrum of different outcomes, and both have agreed that we should be as ambitious as possible. The analysis shows that the modelled White Paper scenario, and the sensitivity modelled around it, would support higher economic output for all sectors, nations and regions than the no deal scenario. The average FTA, EEA-type and no deal scenarios do not deliver the Government’s policy objectives.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-12-03T16:08:12.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016368/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016368/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-11-28","EURATOM","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to EU Exit Long-term economic analysis published on 28 November, which of the four scenarios most accurately reflects the Prime Minister's proposed agreement on the withdrawal of the UK from the EU and Euratom.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","196828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016369","Home Office","false","2018-12-21","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions. The Historical Review identified 14 people who had been detained in an Immigration Removal Centre. Regular updates have been provided to the committee and this information is available in the library of the House. As set out in the letter to the Committee of 12 November, the department initially excluded all individuals with a “criminal case type” marker. We reviewed this approach to ensure we have not adopted too broad a definition and revised our methodology. However, individuals who have been deported following a criminal conviction in the UK continue to be excluded from the review. We will continue to keep the Home Affairs Select Committee updated.</p><p>The Government has committed to establishing a compensation scheme specifically for those members of the Windrush generation who suffered a loss as a result of difficulties in establishing their lawful immigration status. Details of the scheme and how to apply for compensation will be announced as soon as possible. Prior to the launch of the compensation scheme it is open to individuals to bring a claim for compensation through the court system.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196676","2018-12-21T16:59:43.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016369/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016369/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were deported to other countries and have subsequently requested compensation.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016370","Home Office","false","2018-12-21","<p>The Home Office wrote to the Home Affairs Select Committee on 21 August with the initial findings of the Historical Review of removals and detentions. The Historical Review identified 14 people who had been detained in an Immigration Removal Centre. Regular updates have been provided to the committee and this information is available in the library of the House. As set out in the letter to the Committee of 12 November, the department initially excluded all individuals with a “criminal case type” marker. We reviewed this approach to ensure we have not adopted too broad a definition and revised our methodology. However, individuals who have been deported following a criminal conviction in the UK continue to be excluded from the review. We will continue to keep the Home Affairs Select Committee updated.</p><p>The Government has committed to establishing a compensation scheme specifically for those members of the Windrush generation who suffered a loss as a result of difficulties in establishing their lawful immigration status. Details of the scheme and how to apply for compensation will be announced as soon as possible. Prior to the launch of the compensation scheme it is open to individuals to bring a claim for compensation through the court system.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","196675","2018-12-21T16:59:43.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016370/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016370/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-28","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent estimate he has made of the number of members of the Windrush generation who were detained at an immigration centre and have subsequently requested compensation.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","196676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016371","Cabinet Office","false","2018-12-06","<p>The video cost £21,168.72 to produce. The Cabinet Office has spent £90,000 promoting the video on Facebook.</p><p> </p><p>Total annual government communications spend is circa £300m. This activity represents 0.03% of total spend for the year.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-12-06T16:23:40.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016371/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016371/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-11-28","Facebook: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much money from the public purse was spent (a) producing and (b) promoting the Facebook advertisement entitled The Brexit Deal explained.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","196829"
