"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016374","Scotland Office","false","2018-12-06","<p>This video was produced as one of a video series. The approximate cost of production for this individual video was not more than £1,000.</p><p> </p><p>The amount spent on promoting it to date on Facebook has been £311.46.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-12-06T17:41:43.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016374/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016374/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-11-28","Equal Pay: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much money from the public purse was spent (a) producing and (b) promoting the Facebook advertisement entitled Closing the Gender Pay Gap.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","196832"
