"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016378","Cabinet Office","false","2018-12-11","<p>The format of the advert was a video and it started before Facebook's new transparency rules came into effect on the 29 November. The advert finished on the 30 November, while Facebook was still rolling out the ads library to advertisers across the UK, therefore it wasn't placed in the library.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-12-11T17:51:19.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016378/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016378/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-11-28","Facebook: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reason the Facebook advertisement entitled The Brexit Deal explained does not appear in Facebook Ad Library as a political advertisement.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","196836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016379","Scotland Office","false","2018-12-06","<p>This animation was produced in-house and did not incur any production costs.</p><p> </p><p>The amount spent on promoting it to date on Facebook has been £129.78.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-12-06T17:45:16.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016379/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1016379/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-11-28","Public Expenditure: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much money was spent from the public purse (a) producing and (b) promoting the Facebook advertisement entitled Scotland's public spending.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","196837"
